<section class="our-history-section">
    <div class="container">
        <p
            class="section-tagline"
            data-aos="fade-up"
            data-i18n="history_tagline"
        >
            Our Legacy
        </p>
        <h2
            class="section-main-heading"
            data-aos="fade-up"
            data-aos-delay="100"
            data-i18n="history_main_heading"
        >
            A Journey Through Centuries of Faith and Learning
        </h2>

        <div class="history-row" data-aos="fade-up">
            <div class="history-text" data-aos="fade-right">
                <h3
                    class="history-sub-heading"
                    data-i18n="history_from_ancient_heading"
                >
                    From Ancient Roots to New Horizons
                </h3>
                <p data-i18n="history_paragraph_1">
                    Tharlam Monastery, a revered Sakya Buddhist institution
                    whose full name is **Shree Tharlam Sasang Namgyal Ling
                    Monastery**, traces its origins to **1436**. It was
                    originally established by **Ga Rabjampa Kunga Yeshe** in
                    **Kham, Eastern Tibet**, beginning its long and significant
                    journey as a center for Buddhist teachings and practice.
                </p>
                <p data-i18n="history_paragraph_2">
                    Centuries later, its legacy was faithfully rebuilt. In
                    **1981**, the monastery was re-established in **Boudhanath,
                    Kathmandu, Nepal**, by **Dezhung Rinpoche**. This profound
                    re-establishment fulfilled the specific instructions of his
                    guru, **Gaton Dorjechang**, ensuring the spiritual and
                    material continuity of Tharlam Monastery's enduring
                    tradition for future generations.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="history-image" data-aos="fade-left">
                <img
                    src="house.png"
                    alt="Historical image of Tharlam Monastery"
                    class="responsive-image"
                    data-i18n-alt="monastery_image_alt"
                />
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="history-row" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100">
            <div class="history-text" data-aos="fade-right">
                <h3
                    class="history-sub-heading"
                    data-i18n="history_academy_bridging_heading"
                >
                    Tharlam Academy: Bridging Worlds
                </h3>
                <p data-i18n="history_academy_paragraph_1">
                    Tharlam Academy, an integral part of Tharlam Monastery, was
                    established in **1985** right here at the monastery. Its
                    primary purpose was to introduce young monks to essential
                    Western education, including subjects like mathematics,
                    English, science, and various languages. This initiative was
                    crucial, as at that time, Tharlam Monastery primarily
                    focused on teaching rituals and the Tibetan language.
                </p>
                <p data-i18n="history_academy_paragraph_2">
                    Significant improvements began in the early 2000s, enabling
                    the full integration of a comprehensive Western curriculum.
                    Over the past two decades, we have diligently worked to
                    provide the best quality education, allowing our students to
                    excel in subjects like math and science, and become
                    proficient in multiple languages. Today, Tharlam Academy
                    proudly educates around a hundred students, preparing them
                    for both monastic life and the broader world.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="history-image" data-aos="fade-left">
                <img
                    src="house.png"
                    alt="Historical image of Tharlam Academy"
                    class="responsive-image"
                    data-i18n-alt="academy_building_image_alt"
                />
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<style>
    /* Ensure .container is defined globally or locally */
    .container {
        max-width: 1200px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 0 15px;
    }

    /* ============================================== */
    /* 1. HISTORY SECTION STYLES (Mobile First) */
    /* ============================================== */

    .our-history-section {
        padding: 60px 0;
        background-color: #fff; /* White background */
        text-align: center;
    }

    /* --- Section Headings --- */
    .section-tagline {
        color: #004d99; /* Primary Blue */
        font-size: 1.1em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        font-weight: 600;
        margin-bottom: 5px;
    }

    .section-main-heading {
        font-size: 2em; /* Mobile size */
        color: #001f3f;
        font-weight: 700;
        margin-top: 0;
        margin-bottom: 40px;
    }

    /* --- History Rows (Layout) --- */
    .history-row {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column; /* Stack vertically on mobile by default */
        gap: 30px;
        align-items: flex-start;
        text-align: left;
        padding: 30px 0;
        border-bottom: 1px solid #eee; /* Separator between history rows */
    }

    /* Remove border on the last row */
    .history-row:last-child {
        border-bottom: none;
    }

    /* --- Content Blocks (Mobile Order) --- */
    .history-text,
    .history-image {
        width: 100%;
        max-width: 100%;
    }

    .history-image {
        order: 1; /* Image appears first on mobile */
    }
    .history-text {
        order: 2; /* Text appears second on mobile */
    }

    .history-image .responsive-image {
        width: 100%;
        height: auto;
        display: block;
        border-radius: 8px;
        box-shadow: 0 5px 15px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        object-fit: cover;
    }

    .history-sub-heading {
        color: #001f3f;
        font-size: 1.4em;
        margin-bottom: 15px;
        font-weight: 700;
        border-left: 4px solid #004d99; /* Accent bar */
        padding-left: 10px;
    }

    .history-text p {
        font-size: 15px;
        line-height: 1.7;
        color: #555;
        margin-bottom: 15px;
    }

    /* ============================================== */
    /* 2. DESKTOP/LARGE SCREEN (Min-width: 992px) */
    /* ============================================== */
    @media (min-width: 992px) {
        .our-history-section {
            padding: 80px 0;
        }

        .section-main-heading {
            font-size: 2.5em; /* Desktop size */
            margin-bottom: 60px;
        }

        .history-row {
            flex-direction: row; /* Display side-by-side on desktop */
            gap: 50px;
            align-items: center;
        }

        .history-text,
        .history-image {
            flex: 1;
            max-width: 50%;
        }

        /* Desktop Layout Alternation Logic: */

        /* Row 1 (and odd rows): Image Left / Text Right */
        .history-row:nth-child(2n) .history-image {
            order: 1;
        }
        .history-row:nth-child(2n) .history-text {
            order: 2;
        }

        /* Row 2 (and even rows): Text Left / Image Right */
        .history-row:nth-child(2n + 1) .history-text {
            order: 1;
        }
        .history-row:nth-child(2n + 1) .history-image {
            order: 2;
        }

        /* Correction for the very first row to match your AOS (fade-right/fade-left) structure: 
           The HTML provided has Text first, Image second. We flip it here to match the 
           visually expected alternation if the first row is Image-Left. */
        .history-row:nth-child(1) .history-image {
            order: 1; /* Image on Left */
        }
        .history-row:nth-child(1) .history-text {
            order: 2; /* Text on Right */
        }

        .history-sub-heading {
            font-size: 1.6em;
        }

        .history-text p {
            font-size: 16px;
        }
    }
</style>
